Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.04,0:00:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.02,0:00:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But also instilled \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.38,0:00:31.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.26,0:00:42.98,Default,,0,0,30,,Wit is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.98,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,30,,Repress your anguish, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:59.25,Default,,0,0,30,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.25,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,30,,If you win, don't hold your head high, \NIf you lose, don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:14.55,Default,,0,0,30,,Men, don't you ever let others see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:34.91,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.80,0:01:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese Army Type 97 Fighter. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nakajima_Ki-27}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.45,0:01:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This fighter plane boasted high maneuverability,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.69,0:01:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but the tradeoff had been \Nits extremely short cruising range.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.69,0:01:53.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\an6\move(1300,600,1170,650,0,5150)\t(0,5150,\fs70)\blur1\bord0\b\q2\c&HD4CCC4&}Dauntless \N\N\N\N\N\NSpitfire \N\N\N\N\NHurricane\N\N\N\N\N\NType 97 Fighter {九七式戦闘機}\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NCruising range (km) {航続距離}                                                                       \h
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.53,0:01:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,For that reason, ever since 1939,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.75,0:01:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,those responsible for air operations \Nin the Imperial Headquarters Army Department
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.83,0:02:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,were desperately trying to modernize it \Nin accordance with contemporary warfare. {lit: preparing for modern warfare, they were desperately doing this improvement - no clue what it means; 近代戦に備えてこの改良に必死であった}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.47,0:02:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result of countless modifications and experiments,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.07,0:02:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,a newly-designed aircraft was born, furnished with \Nthe same engine as the Navy's cutting-edge Zero fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.99,0:02:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Two 12.7 mm machine guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.82,0:02:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A top speed of 515 km/h.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.32,0:02:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The fatal flaw of the previous model, \Na short cruising range,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.01,0:02:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,was rectified through the installation \Nof an auxiliary drop tank under the wing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.42,0:02:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the pride of Japan on the world stage, \Nthe Type 1 Falcon Fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.19,0:03:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The commander of the 64th Squadron, \NMajor Kato Takeo
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.80,0:03:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,took it upon himself to display the efficiency of the "Falcon"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.21,0:03:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,by initiating an intense flying drill with his unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.49,0:03:28.94,Sign,,0,0,250,,{\fade(300,400)\b1\bord0\blur1\c&HF4F2F1&}Episode 14\N{\fs100}Kato's Falcon Squadron
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.50,0:03:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,First, in December 1941,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.67,0:03:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the 64th Squadron under the command of Major Kato
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.30,0:03:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,supported a large invasion force {actually "large fleet, escorting the landing parties"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.38,0:03:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Malay Peninsula under the command \Nof Lieutenant General Tomoyuki Yamashita.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.46,0:03:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They flew from Phu Quoc Island in Indochina \Nto Nakhon in Thailand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.46,0:03:48.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\q2\fs60\bord0\b1\blur1\move(0,0,800,-400)\c&HD7D8E6&}\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h        Gulf of Thailand\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                                                    Phu Quoc Island \N\N\N\N\N\N\N{\c&HDDE7E5&}Nakhon                                                                                  \h{\NMalay Peninsula\NKota Bharu}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.17,0:03:51.38,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\q2\fs60\bord0\b1\blur1\move(800,-400,1250,-650)\c&HD7D8E6&}\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h        Gulf of Thailand\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                                                    Phu Quoc Island \N\N\N\N\N\N\N{\c&HDDE7E5&}Nakhon                                                                                  \h\N{Malay Peninsula\NKota Bharu}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.31,0:03:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,After completing its mission, \Nthe Kato Falcon Squadron
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.36,0:03:56.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\q2\fs60\bord0\b1\blur1\move(1250,-650,500,-1300)\c&HD7D8E6&}\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h        Gulf of Thailand\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                                                    Phu Quoc Island \N\N\N\N\N\N\N{\c&HDDE7E5&}Nakhon                                                                                  \h\N\N\N\N\N\N\N{\frz-50} \h                                                                                                                                                                                           Malay Peninsula\N{\frz}\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                              Kota Bharu
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.30,0:03:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,proceeded further south \Nto a forward Kota Bharu base in Malaysia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.17,0:04:05.06,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1400)\q2\fs60\bord0\b1\blur1\move(500,-1300,400,-2500,1400,9000)\c&HCED6D3&\t(1400,9000,\fs100)}\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h        Gulf of Thailand\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                                                    Phu Quoc Island \N\N\N\N\N\N\N{\c&HDDE7E5&}Nakhon                                                                                  \h\N\N\N\N\N\N\N{\frz-50} \h                                                                                                                                                                                           Malay Peninsula\N{\frz}\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                              Kota Bharu
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.94,0:04:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The tremendous pace of their advance \Nwould later be called miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.57,0:04:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Our landing party continued its blitzkrieg, advancing all the way to the Perak River on the Malay Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.22,0:04:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if the enemy destroys the bridge over it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.16,0:04:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll delay the fall of Singapore, the ultimate goal \Nof the Malay blitzkrieg, by three months at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.50,0:04:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Falcon Squadron will be tasked \Nwith preventing that act of sabotage
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.92,0:04:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,by keeping a constant air patrol \Nfrom the Alor Star air base. {lit: would move to ... to be staying in the air; remaining airborne} {Very unsure I got the city name right, but it had an air base so gotta be it}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.50,0:04:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To destroy the bridge, the enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.65,0:04:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,would be likely to use planes from Kuala Lumpur. { air base} {very unsure he means this, but I see noo ther explanation; destroying bridges by planes was a very unsuccessful endeavor even at the end of the war, leave alone in 1941 but outdated and outnumbered planes}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.30,0:04:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, those giving orders in the army aviation division
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.18,0:04:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,don't realize that we here at the Falcon Squadron \Naren't about patiently waiting for the enemy to come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.13,0:04:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take the initiative \Nand smash the enemy aircraft in Kuala Lumpur. {/go out first ourselves}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.75,0:04:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my impromptu order. { one's own judgement (judgment); decision made without consulting others; arbitrary decision}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.57,0:04:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.36,0:04:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.91,0:05:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Takayama. Let me take a picture first. {no clue if I heard the name right}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.31,0:05:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.97,0:05:35.38,Song,,0,0,0,,The engine roars like thunder {Enjin no oto gogoto}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.38,0:05:43.51,Song,,0,0,0,,The Falcon conquers the edge of the clouds {hayabusa wa yuku no hate}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.13,0:05:48.44,Song,,0,0,0,,The Rising Suns shining on our wings {Yoku ni kagayaku hinomaru to}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.44,0:05:52.08,Song,,0,0,0,,And the Red Eagles drawn on our chests {Mune ni egaki shi akawashi no}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.08,0:06:01.52,Song,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1000)} Those are the symbols of our fighters {Shirushi wa warera ga sentotai}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.49,0:06:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Kuala Lumpur.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.77,0:06:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.58,0:07:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.00,0:07:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take you to hell with me! {believing HA, no clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.63,0:07:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, comrades... Goodbye! {no clue what's the word after kaicho}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.43,0:08:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The assault on Kuala Lumpur \Nwas Major Kato's unauthorized order.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.65,0:08:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But contrary to the expectations, the commander's ability \Nto stay collected and adapt to the situation at hand
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.22,0:08:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1400)}was praised by the Southern Expeditionary Army's Commander-in-Chief in a congratulatory telegram.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.27,0:08:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Takayama. This photo I took of you \Nended up becoming your last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.72,0:08:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.45,0:08:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be alone in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.67,0:09:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,On January 9th, the 64th Falcon Squadron, \Ncommanded by Major Kato
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.14,0:09:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,proceeded further south to the air base in Ipoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.03,0:09:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,From this base, they raid Singapore daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Aided by allied heavy bombers, \Nthey succeeded in bombing the Singapore Air Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.51,0:09:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, without encountering the enemy fighter unit \Nwith the Hurricane as its core,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.94,0:09:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the Falcon Squadron's decisive battle \Ndidn't really feel all that decisive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.29,0:09:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,On January 29th, in order to support the Japanese Singapore bombing unit that sortied from Kota Bharu,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.68,0:09:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Major Kato was about to take off \Nwith a handful of other planes from his squadron.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.71,0:10:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Still not fixed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.95,0:10:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We needs just a little more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.79,0:10:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have it. I'll go ahead. {/can't wait}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.65,0:10:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Omori, catch up with us later, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.73,0:10:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger! Will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.06,0:10:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,However, upon arrival, they never found \Nthe allied bombers they were supposed to support.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.04,0:10:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So they had no choice but to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.00,0:10:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming late. I gotta catch up \Nwith the commander and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.39,0:10:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's our bombing unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.07,0:10:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But the commander isn't here to support them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.20,0:11:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it. If it came to this, I'll deal with you alone! {lit: I'll be your opponent - one plane }
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.81,0:11:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The commander is in a bad mood and won't talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.60,0:11:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought. \NBecause we failed to support them...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.09,0:12:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He wouldn't even eat his dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.01,0:12:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Omori!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.84,0:12:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.32,0:12:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I fought back with just one plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.56,0:12:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what about our bombers?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.85,0:12:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Two planes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.55,0:12:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,...Got shot down?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.49,0:12:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me if you can...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.55,0:12:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This blunder will stay with me forever. {nc what's first word, prolly kato no; lit: lifelong mistake}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.78,0:13:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, sir. An emergency telegram arrived \Nfrom the bombing unit that sortied to Singapore today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.80,0:13:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.69,0:13:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In that telegram, they thanked Sergeant Major Omori
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.50,0:14:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for courageously supporting them and shooting down two Hurricanes with just one aircraft in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.18,0:14:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It was noted that the two downed allied bombers made an emergency landing, and all their crew members were safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.30,0:14:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? So they've been rescued?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.26,0:14:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank god. Thank god!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.40,0:14:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,With Kato's Falcon Squadron spearheading the way, \Nin the face of the Japanese aviation corps' success,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.39,0:14:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the systematic resistance, \Nput up by the Royal Air Force had all but disappeared. {unsure what he means: 日本軍航空部隊の活躍の前にイギリス空軍の組織的な挑戦はほとんどなくなった }
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, Lieutenant General Yamashita Tomoyuki's unit, tasked with overrunning the Malay Peninsula
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.29,0:14:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,was now also one step closer to Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.29,0:14:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in their daily battles,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.35,0:14:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the Kato Falcon Squadron \Nkept suffering considerable losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.47,0:14:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Around that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.81,0:14:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the plans were being drawn \Nfor the capture of the Palembang oil fields intact
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.41,0:15:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,by the forces of the Japanese Army's first paratrooper unit. {unsure why he says 最初の instead of first}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.28,0:15:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,On February 5th, Major Kato \Nrushed to the Cruz base alone {nc what's this Cruz base HA mentions, but i've no clue what else kurusu kichi can be either; it's kinda a common toponym I think?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.51,0:15:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet with the 3rd Squadron Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.94,0:15:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy troops are concentrating in Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.86,0:15:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Palembang should be captured \Nbefore Singapore surrenders.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.86,0:15:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,As the aerial photography shows, \Nthe enemy air base in Palembang is hidden in the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.24,0:15:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,On it, they amassed about a hundred planes, \Nranging from big to small.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.66,0:15:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to ensure a safe landing for the paratroopers, \Nfirst, we must secure air superiority by dogfighting. {航空撃滅戦 is "aerial destruction combat" so I think he means destroy them from air, but with fighters, as opposed to bombing}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.81,0:15:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Please assign that mission to my squadron.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.77,0:15:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Your squadron has lost \Na considerable part of its strength in the previous battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.81,0:15:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can barely provide any support \Nwith your current strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.69,0:15:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, our strength has waned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.99,0:15:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.51,0:15:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Our spirit is still strong! {/is enough}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.68,0:15:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll succeed, I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.67,0:15:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let us do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.14,0:16:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I can't stop you anyhow, can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.05,0:16:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
