Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.25,0:16:14.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs70\t(1,\fs100)\an5\fade(0,2000)\q2\c&HCFCDC6&\bord0\blur1\b1\move(1487,690,250,-1364)}{\frz-60}Malay Peninsula \N\N\N\N\h
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.03,0:16:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, in preparation for the air battle for Palembang, \NKato's Falcon Squadron {/dogfighting over ...}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.91,0:16:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced further south, \Nmaking Kahang its forward base.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.45,0:16:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Our squadron will work in cooperation \Nwith the light bombers of the 3rd Air Corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.82,0:16:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to destroy the enemy planes in Palembang.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.03,0:16:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever happens, we have to succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.27,0:16:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,To that end, I expect everyone to distinguish himself, {そのためには自分一人の手柄に発し出す - unsure}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.13,0:16:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,putting on display the true strength \Nof our entire unit until the bitter end. {あくまで部隊全体の力を発揮するよう各自心を挙げてほしい - unsure what to make of the "raise the heart" part, prolly just means "be brave"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.01,0:16:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They started by conducting a raid \Non the British base in Palembang.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.73,0:16:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And later, on February 4th, the Falcon Fighter Squadron \Nsortied to support the paratrooper units.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.87,0:16:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Through their determined effort, \Nthe successful occupation of Palembang was achieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.17,0:16:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The Falcon Fighter Squadron \Nhad no time to catch their breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.08,0:16:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,With the conclusion of action in Palembang, \Nthey were transferred to Chiang Mai, Thailand. {sounds really more like tairyo than thailand, likely actually means "mass transit/in large quantities" but w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.85,0:17:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,From there they started raiding \Nthe Akyab base in Burma on a daily basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.53,0:17:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.69,0:17:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.75,0:17:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Good job, everyone. \NHere's the next order.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.10,0:17:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The squadron should immediately \Nhit and expel the remaining enemies in the area. {no clue whatsoever what's rougen here, could be "experienced; veteran; skilled; expert" or "beacon; skyrocket; signal fire; smoke signals" neither of which makes sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.56,0:17:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? There's still more to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.91,0:17:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,At war, you have to work around the clock. {lit: combatant/fighter is day and night}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.15,0:17:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Being at all times on the call is our ultimate mission. {lit: mobilization; going into action; being dispatched; being sent out; being called in; turning out system/organization}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.95,0:18:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit! We keep beating them, \Nbut they keep coming back! {叩いても叩いてもすぐ出てきやがる - lit: we hit and hit them, but another one shows up at once}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.21,0:18:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, Major Kato was showered in letters of admiration for his remarkable achievements
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.32,0:18:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and was promoted to Lieutenant Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.01,0:18:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,On May 21st, he was pursuing a British bomber, \Nbut lost sight of it over Chittagong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.74,0:18:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Shimizu! {beliving HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.02,0:18:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Shimizu, I'll be sure to come back for you. Just you wait! {/come to look for you}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.84,0:18:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow in the afternoon we're moving out \Nand transferring to the Toungoo base.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.74,0:19:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,By then, I'd like to send a search and rescue mission \Nafter Lieutenant Shimizu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.83,0:19:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Roger that. I'll have the local volunteer army \Ndo their best to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.25,0:19:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.38,0:19:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Near noon on the next day, the 22nd, \Nthe Falcon Squadron
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.71,0:19:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,completed preparations for moving to Toungoo base \Nto continue destroying the Allied Air Force from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.10,0:19:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They were just waiting \Nfor Lieutenant Colonel Kato's sortie order.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.91,0:19:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Colonel, it's time to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.42,0:19:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's wait a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.37,0:19:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The commander sure is taking his time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.43,0:19:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's two hours past the scheduled time already.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.39,0:19:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Shimizu, please come back safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.48,0:20:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Colonel, you have to leave now. {lit: it's time already}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.99,0:20:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.66,0:20:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Lieutenant Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.21,0:20:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.57,0:20:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Shimizu! Shimizu is back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.36,0:20:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out! It's the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.19,0:21:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.47,0:21:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Start me up! {beliving HA, no clue what he actually says; makes sense as mawase is to spin/rotate}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.10,0:21:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Start me up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.39,0:21:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.24,0:21:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit! I'll avenge Shimizu!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.19,0:22:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.13,0:22:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.33,0:22:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.60,0:23:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, the 64th Falcon Squadron Commander, \NLieutenant Colonel Kato Takeo
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.74,0:23:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,found his eternal rest \Ndeep on the seabed of the Bay of Bengal {lit: at the deep bottom of ... forever became a non-returnee}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.21,0:23:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,on May 22, 2:30 p.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.96,0:23:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Lieutenant Colonel Kato kept on living.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.05,0:23:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,His indomitable fighting spirit and determination \Nlived on in the hearts of his men.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.87,0:24:07.65,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.\NBut also instilled numerous lessons on how to live.{太平洋戦争はわれわれに平和の尊さを教えたがまた生きるための教訓を数多くのこしている}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.47,0:24:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Summer of 1943.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.99,0:24:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese forward base at Rabaul
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.22,0:24:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is constantly under attack from the American army.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.06,0:24:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the task force that was supposed to bring in reinforcements abandoned the men of the Rabaul Air Corps
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.39,0:24:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as they found themselves amidst the American forces, \Nadvancing like a tidal wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.46,0:24:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Unsurprisingly, they never made it back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.13,0:24:38.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 15\NRabaul Air Corps {ラバウル航空隊}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.13,0:24:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Look forward to next week's Decision:\NRabaul Air Corps.
Comment: 0,0:24:43.11,0:24:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.90,0:24:48.68,Default,,0,0,50,,If you're a man, let's put your strength to test{男だったら　力を試せ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.68,0:24:52.80,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, keep your hopes sizzling{男だったら　希望(のぞみ)を燃やせ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.80,0:24:57.16,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, don't lose your heart{男だったら　くじけるな}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.16,0:25:05.73,Default,,0,0,50,,Because there's just you and me, a man and a man{俺もおまえも　男と男}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.73,0:25:14.11,Default,,0,0,50,,With crimson blood flowing in our veins all the same{おなじ真赤な　血が通う}
